**Emergencies in Japan**

Ensuring the safety and security of U.S. citizens overseas is the Department of State’s top priority. U.S. citizens needing urgent assistance should contact us by using our [inquiry form](https://jp.usembassy.gov/contact/) or phone (03-3224-5000). If you need after-hours assistance in an emergency, please call 03-3224-5000 and ask to speak with the Embassy’s duty officer.

Things to do
https://www.tripadvisor.com/Attractions-g1066451-Activities-Minato_Tokyo_Tokyo_Prefecture_Kanto.html 
	LandMarks
			Visit some of Tokyo's famous landmarks, such as [Tokyo Tower](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tokyo_Tower), the [Tokyo Metropolitan Government Building](https://www.japan-guide.com/e/e3011_tocho.html), and the [Tokyo Skytree](https://www.tokyo-skytree.jp/en/).
	Neighborhoods
		Explore Tokyo's many neighborhoods and districts, such as [Asakusa](https://www.japan-guide.com/e/e3004.html), [Ginza](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ginza), and [Shibuya](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shibuya). Each neighborhood has its own unique character and charm, and you'll be able to find something for everyone.
	Temples and Shrines
		Visit some of Tokyo's temples and shrines, such as [Meiji Shrine](https://www.japan-guide.com/e/e3002.html) and [Senso-ji Temple](https://www.japan-guide.com/e/e3001.html). These are important cultural and historical sites that offer a glimpse into Japan's rich history and religion.
	Culinary
		Sample some of Tokyo's delicious food. Tokyo is known for its street food, sushi, and ramen, and you'll be able to find a wide variety of delicious dishes to try.
		[Sushi Dai](https://www.thewholeworldisaplayground.com/how-to-eat-seat-sushi-dai-tokyo-tips-guide/) Located in the bustling Tsukiji Fish Market, Sushi Dai is a popular spot for fresh sushi and other seafood dishes. The restaurant has a reputation for serving some of the best sushi in Tokyo, and it is often crowded with tourists and locals alike.
		[Tonkatsu Maisen](https://trulytokyo.com/maisen/): This tonkatsu (breaded and fried pork cutlet) chain is known for its high-quality ingredients and perfectly crispy pork. The restaurant has several locations around the city, including a flagship store in the trendy Omotesando neighborhood.
		[Tempura Kondo](https://tempura-kondo.com/en/): Located in the Ginza district, Tempura Kondo is a Michelin-starred tempura restaurant that is renowned for its light, delicate tempura dishes. The restaurant has a traditional atmosphere and serves set meals featuring a variety of tempura dishes.
		[Narisawa](https://www.narisawa-yoshihiro-en.com/): This two-Michelin-starred restaurant in the Meguro neighborhood is known for its innovative, artistic dishes that showcase the natural flavors of locally sourced ingredients. The restaurant's menus change seasonally, and reservations are highly recommended.
		[Yakiniku Jumbo](https://valuet.co.jp/brands/jumbo): This chain of yakiniku (grilled meat) restaurants is a popular spot for affordable and delicious grilled meat dishes. The restaurants have a laid-back atmosphere and offer a wide selection of meats and other dishes to grill at your table.
	Markets
		These markets are great places to try local food and find souvenirs.
		[Tsukiji Fish Market ](https://www.japan-guide.com/e/e3021.html)
		[Ameyoko Market](https://www.japan-guide.com/e/e3012.html)
	Parks
		Take a walk through one of Tokyo's many parks. These parks are great places to relax and take in the sights and sounds of the city.
		[Yoyogi Park](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yoyogi_Park)
		[Ueno Park](https://www.japan-guide.com/e/e3019.html)
